GM’s Opel Sells Cars at Record 30% Discount, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-03-27T12:37:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/gm-s-opel-sells-cars-at-record-30-discount-handelsblatt-says.html
General Motors Corp.’s Adam Opel
unit sells car at a higher discount than any other German
carmaker,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing a survey by Duisburg-
Essen University.  Opel offers discounts of as much as 30 percent for its
Astra vehicle, a competitor to  Volkswagen AG (VOW) ’s Golf, which is
being sold with a discount of as much as ten percent, the
newspaper said in an e-mailed preview of a report to be
published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net . 